{"article_id":"kN0SfHuegZEdap5L","edus":[{"id":0,"text":"( CNN )","depth":1},{"id":1,"text":"This story has been updated","depth":3},{"id":2,"text":"following the primaries in Kentucky and Oregon .","depth":3},{"id":3,"text":"Bernie Sanders , in response to Hillary Clinton 's significant delegate lead , has called for wholesale changes to the Democratic Party 's primary system ,","depth":8},{"id":4,"text":"suggesting","depth":9},{"id":5,"text":"that is it both un-democratic","depth":10},{"id":6,"text":"and tilted in favor of the former secretary of state .","depth":10},{"id":7,"text":"The use of superdelegates , essentially free-agent delegates","depth":9},{"id":8,"text":"comprised mostly of Democratic Party stalwarts ,","depth":10},{"id":9,"text":"many of whom are already backing Clinton ,","depth":10},{"id":10,"text":"is the primary complaint .","depth":8},{"id":11,"text":"But","depth":8},{"id":12,"text":"based on CNN 's analysis ,","depth":8},{"id":13,"text":"major changes to the ways","depth":9},{"id":14,"text":"Democrats allocate their delegates ,","depth":9},{"id":15,"text":"or even abolishing superdelegates , would still result in Clinton holding a large lead over Sanders and close to winning the nomination .","depth":8},{"id":16,"text":"Here 's Sanders ' path to the nomination , and the results of some alternate scenarios","depth":7},{"id":17,"text":"for deciding the Democratic nominee :","depth":7},{"id":18,"text":"At this point , Sanders can not clinch the nomination","depth":12},{"id":19,"text":"based on the amount of pledged delegates","depth":13},{"id":20,"text":"remaining alone","depth":13},{"id":21,"text":"-- he would need to win 110 % of the remaining pledged delegates available","depth":12},{"id":22,"text":"to reach the magic number of 2,383 ,","depth":12},{"id":23,"text":"according to CNN estimates .","depth":10},{"id":24,"text":"But he still has a mathematical chance","depth":10},{"id":25,"text":"of winning more pledged delegates than Clinton ,","depth":11},{"id":26,"text":"which would help him persuade enough of the 700-plus superdelegates","depth":12},{"id":27,"text":"to put him over the top .","depth":12},{"id":28,"text":"Since their inception in the 1980s , superdelegates have by and large supported the candidate with the most pledged delegates","depth":11},{"id":29,"text":"going into the convention .","depth":11},{"id":30,"text":"'' `` It is a steep hill to climb ,","depth":13},{"id":31,"text":"and I acknowledge that ,","depth":13},{"id":32,"text":"but we have the possibility","depth":14},{"id":33,"text":"of walking into the Democratic convention with a majority of pledged delegates , ''","depth":14},{"id":34,"text":"Sanders said last week in California .","depth":13},{"id":35,"text":"To accomplish that ,","depth":13},{"id":36,"text":"Sanders will need to win about 70 % of all remaining pledged delegates in the final nine contests ,","depth":14},{"id":37,"text":"according to CNN estimates .","depth":14},{"id":38,"text":"That would be a significant jump from his performance in the previous 48 contests ,","depth":13},{"id":39,"text":"where he has won only about 45 % of the pledged delegates .","depth":13},{"id":40,"text":"Sanders could pull this off","depth":11},{"id":41,"text":"by crushing Clinton in the remaining contests by a 2-to-1 margin .","depth":11},{"id":42,"text":"But he 's only been able to accomplish that in eight races ,","depth":11},{"id":43,"text":"and he has n't hit that level of support since March .","depth":11},{"id":44,"text":"Looking at the calendar ,","depth":10},{"id":45,"text":"Sanders could run up his numbers in Kentucky , Oregon , Montana , North Dakota and South Dakota .","depth":10},{"id":46,"text":"But those states , combined , offer fewer delegates than two upcoming contests","depth":11},{"id":47,"text":"where Clinton is expected to perform well :","depth":11},{"id":48,"text":"Puerto Rico and New Jersey .","depth":10},{"id":49,"text":"So","depth":9},{"id":50,"text":"for Sanders to finish with a majority of pledged delegates ,","depth":10},{"id":51,"text":"he would likely need a blowout of epic proportions in California .","depth":10},{"id":52,"text":"The key complaint from critics of the nomination process is about the 700-plus superdelegates , free agents","depth":6},{"id":53,"text":"who can vote for anyone of their choosing .","depth":6},{"id":54,"text":"They are primarily Democratic members of Congress , governors , mayors and union officials and loyalists .","depth":5},{"id":55,"text":"JUST WATCHED","depth":10},{"id":56,"text":"Could Sanders revolt upend Democratic convention ?","depth":10},{"id":57,"text":"Replay More Videos ...","depth":9},{"id":58,"text":"MUST WATCH","depth":10},{"id":59,"text":"Could Sanders revolt upend Democratic convention ?","depth":10},{"id":60,"text":"02:10","depth":9},{"id":61,"text":"Clinton has endorsements from 521 superdelegates ,","depth":10},{"id":62,"text":"and Sanders only has 41 ,","depth":10},{"id":63,"text":"according to CNN 's count as of May 18 .","depth":9},{"id":64,"text":"Given the choice between a longtime party leader , and a political insurgent","depth":11},{"id":65,"text":"who only became a Democrat last year ,","depth":11},{"id":66,"text":"the party elite has clearly rallied behind Clinton .","depth":10},{"id":67,"text":"This commanding lead among superdelegates has pushed Clinton toward officially clinching the nomination .","depth":10},{"id":68,"text":"But it has also led to complaints from Sanders","depth":11},{"id":69,"text":"that the system is unfair .","depth":11},{"id":70,"text":"`` I would hope very much","depth":9},{"id":71,"text":"that the superdelegates from those states","depth":13},{"id":72,"text":"where we have won with big margins","depth":14},{"id":73,"text":"or , in fact , where Secretary Clinton has won with big margins ,","depth":14},{"id":74,"text":"to respect the wishes of the people of those states","depth":12},{"id":75,"text":"and vote in line with how the people of that state voted , ''","depth":11},{"id":76,"text":"Sanders said last week at a speech in Washington .","depth":10},{"id":77,"text":"If the superdelegates from each state were to be awarded as a bloc to the candidate","depth":12},{"id":78,"text":"who wins each primary ,","depth":12},{"id":79,"text":"Sanders would benefit ,","depth":11},{"id":80,"text":"but still face an uphill climb .","depth":10},{"id":81,"text":"'' JUST WATCHED","depth":10},{"id":82,"text":"Sanders campaign :","depth":11},{"id":83,"text":"Democrats 'court disaster ' in Clinton","depth":11},{"id":84,"text":"Replay More Videos ...","depth":11},{"id":85,"text":"MUST WATCH","depth":12},{"id":86,"text":"Sanders campaign :","depth":13},{"id":87,"text":"Democrats 'court disaster ' in Clinton","depth":13},{"id":88,"text":"01:32","depth":10},{"id":89,"text":"Clinton would have 384 superdelegates , to Sanders ' 177 .","depth":11},{"id":90,"text":"Following these rules ,","depth":12},{"id":91,"text":"Sanders would have to win about 74 % of the remaining pledged delegates","depth":13},{"id":92,"text":"to clinch the nomination .","depth":13},{"id":93,"text":"Right now , Sanders has 13 superdelegates in states","depth":13},{"id":94,"text":"Clinton won ,","depth":13},{"id":95,"text":"according to CNN 's delegate estimate .","depth":12},{"id":96,"text":"Sanders aides have told CNN","depth":13},{"id":97,"text":"they will not ask superdelegates from those states to back Clinton .","depth":13},{"id":98,"text":"This includes states like Florida , Mississippi and North Carolina , all states","depth":13},{"id":99,"text":"Clinton won by double digits .","depth":13},{"id":100,"text":"What if superdelegates were treated like pledged delegates ,","depth":9},{"id":101,"text":"divided up proportionally ,","depth":10},{"id":102,"text":"based on the popular vote in each state ?","depth":10},{"id":103,"text":"JUST WATCHED","depth":8},{"id":104,"text":"The math does n't favor Bernie Sanders ,","depth":9},{"id":105,"text":"despite wins","depth":9},{"id":106,"text":"Replay More Videos ...","depth":9},{"id":107,"text":"MUST WATCH","depth":12},{"id":108,"text":"The math does n't favor Bernie Sanders ,","depth":13},{"id":109,"text":"despite wins","depth":13},{"id":110,"text":"02:11","depth":11},{"id":111,"text":"The Maine Democratic Party recently voted to implement this proposal","depth":13},{"id":112,"text":"starting in 2020 .","depth":13},{"id":113,"text":"Sanders praised the decision","depth":13},{"id":114,"text":"and said","depth":14},{"id":115,"text":"he hopes","depth":15},{"id":116,"text":"`` other states follow Maine 's example . ''","depth":15},{"id":117,"text":"It 's a scenario","depth":13},{"id":118,"text":"that benefits Sanders even more","depth":14},{"id":119,"text":"than awarding them all to the winner .","depth":14},{"id":120,"text":"That 's because he would earn a chunk of delegates from states like New York and Illinois ,","depth":14},{"id":121,"text":"where he got close ,","depth":15},{"id":122,"text":"but did not beat Clinton .","depth":15},{"id":123,"text":"Clinton would have 296 superdelegates ,","depth":14},{"id":124,"text":"and Sanders would have 265 .","depth":14},{"id":125,"text":"Even with these rules , Sanders would still need about 69 % of remaining pledged delegates","depth":9},{"id":126,"text":"to clinch the nomination .","depth":9},{"id":127,"text":"Superdelegates have become a political problem for the second contested Democratic contest in a row .","depth":9},{"id":128,"text":"In 2008 , Barack Obama took the overall lead in pledged delegates","depth":11},{"id":129,"text":"and used that","depth":12},{"id":130,"text":"to convince more and more superdelegates to back him ,","depth":12},{"id":131,"text":"and Hillary Clinton eventually ended her run .","depth":10},{"id":132,"text":"In both 2016 and 2008 , the question is about fairness .","depth":9},{"id":133,"text":"Why should a group of several hundred party regulars be in a position","depth":10},{"id":134,"text":"to potentially limit or overturn the will of the voters ?","depth":10},{"id":135,"text":"Democratic National Committee Chairwoman Debbie Wasserman Schultz said","depth":8},{"id":136,"text":"the superdelegates are meant to essentially reinforce the position of the winner in pledged delegates .","depth":8},{"id":137,"text":"JUST WATCHED","depth":8},{"id":138,"text":"The KY & OR primaries on CNN in 60 seconds","depth":8},{"id":139,"text":"Replay More Videos ...","depth":8},{"id":140,"text":"MUST WATCH The KY & OR primaries on CNN in 60 seconds 01:07","depth":8},{"id":141,"text":"`` Unpledged delegates exist really","depth":9},{"id":142,"text":"to make sure","depth":10},{"id":143,"text":"that party leaders and elected officials do n't have to be in a position","depth":11},{"id":144,"text":"where they are running against grass-roots activists , ''","depth":11},{"id":145,"text":"she told CNN 's Jake Tapper in February .","depth":8},{"id":146,"text":"`` We are , as a Democratic Party , really highlight and emphasize inclusiveness and diversity at our convention ,","depth":8},{"id":147,"text":"and so we want to give every opportunity to grass-roots activists and diverse committed Democrats","depth":9},{"id":148,"text":"to be able to participate , attend and be a delegate at the convention . ''","depth":9},{"id":149,"text":"So what would happen","depth":7},{"id":150,"text":"if superdelegates were eliminated from the 2016 race ?","depth":7},{"id":151,"text":"According to the math ,","depth":8},{"id":152,"text":"the results would be about the same","depth":9},{"id":153,"text":"of awarding them proportionally .","depth":9},{"id":154,"text":"Eliminating the superdelegates would lower the threshold","depth":11},{"id":155,"text":"needed","depth":12},{"id":156,"text":"to clinch the nomination","depth":12},{"id":157,"text":"to 2,026 delegates .","depth":10},{"id":158,"text":"Clinton would still be leading Sanders by nearly 300 delegates .","depth":9},{"id":159,"text":"Under this scenario , Clinton would still only need to win about 33 % of the remaining delegates","depth":9},{"id":160,"text":"to become the Democratic nominee .","depth":9}],"relations":[{"parent":321,"left":0,"right":320,"relation":"organization","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":320,"left":162,"right":319,"relation":"context","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":162,"left":1,"right":2,"relation":"context","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":319,"left":213,"right":318,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":213,"left":210,"right":212,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":210,"left":174,"right":209,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":174,"left":169,"right":173,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":169,"left":165,"right":168,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":165,"left":3,"right":164,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":164,"left":4,"right":163,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":163,"left":5,"right":6,"relation":"joint","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":168,"left":167,"right":10,"relation":"same-unit","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":167,"left":7,"right":166,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":166,"left":8,"right":9,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":173,"left":170,"right":172,"relation":"same-unit","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":170,"left":11,"right":12,"relation":"attribution","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":172,"left":171,"right":15,"relation":"same-unit","nuclearity":"NN"},{"parent":171,"left":13,"right":14,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":209,"left":175,"right":208,"relation":"organization","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":175,"left":16,"right":17,"relation":"purpose","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":208,"left":200,"right":207,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":200,"left":184,"right":199,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":184,"left":180,"right":183,"relation":"adversative","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":180,